	(525,60,'','','Thai Tan','Rocketbook Wave: Cloud Connected Microwavable Notebook','rocketbook-wave-cloud-connected-microwavable-notebook','<div></div><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Are you the type of person who loves to take hand written notes or jot down hand written ideas, but then finds yourself frustrated when needing to send notes to others or transfer thoughts onto the computer?<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Well the Rocketbook Wave is here to help solve this problem. The Rocketbook is a new way to take and record notes. Simply use one of these advances notebooks, (ranging in size from 5.8in x 8.9in to 8.5in x 9.5in), with a Pilot Frixion ink pen (available with purchase of a Rocketbook notebook, as well as at most office supply stores), then take a picture of your work via the free mobile app, and watch as the app produces a high quality, clear image of your work and then automatically crops the image down so just the page is showing, and finally uploads the work to your cloud. That\'s not all this special notebook can do however; this notebook also comes with seven different symbols located at the bottom of every page which users can assign to specific folders within their clouds. After the completion of a page, the user can choose which folder they would like their information to be uploaded to, by malting the corresponding symbol on that page, thereby eliminating the need to go back through and organize the work later. Furthermore, the Rocketbook notebooks are actually reusable! When a notebook is filled, simply place it in the microwave with a mug of water on top, and heat until the &#34;Wave&#34; logo, turns from blue to white, the. Pull it out and start filling it with your thoughts again! Reusable for up to 10 uses, this new notebook revolutionizes the art of note taking and is a must have for any modern day student or business person.</span></p><ul><li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s2\"></span><span class=\"s1\">Upload notes, sketc